<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-104-986  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 104 986.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Feb 20 1989 v6 n7 p57(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Access, Cognos join hands on 20-20 Database Connection. (AccessTechnology Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Access Technology and Cognos formed a technological alliance tojointly develop new software products.andP;  The result of thatagreement is the 20-20 Database Connection, a bridge betweenCognos' PowerHouse fourth-generation development language andAccess' 20-20 spreadsheet software.andP;  The bridge will provide afast way for users to retrieve information from PowerHouseapplications and to import it into the spreadsheet without havingto re-key it.andP;  Users do not need to be trained in a querylanguage, since English-language menus help the user to buildappropriate queries.andP;  The 20-20 Database Connection costs between$800 when purchased for the MicroVAX 2000 and $17,000 whenpurchased for the VAX 8978.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cognos (product introduction)Access Technology Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   20-20 Database Connection (Computer program) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     DEXPO East - The DEC-Compatible Exposition and ConferenceCooperative AgreementProduct DevelopmentSpreadsheetsData Base Management SystemsGateways (Interface)Product Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Access, Cognos Join Hands On 20/20 Database ConnectionandM;NEW YORK -- Both Access Technology and Cognos have been attempting tostrengthen their market position over the past year by forming technologicalalliances with several companies--including each other.andM;As a result of a development agreement reached in June, Access and Cognos atDexpo East here earlier this month made the 20/20 Database Connectionavailable for PowerHouse, Cognos' fourth-generation development language.andO;The 20/20 Database Connection will be marketed, sold and serviced by bothcompanies.andP;  Access officials said the new connection will provide users witha bridge--a quick and easy way to retrieve information from a PowerHouseapplication and then bring it into a 20/20 spreadsheet for reporting andanalysis.andM;&quot;You can take standard data on the VAX, bring it to the workstation andmanipulate it any way you want to [on 20/20] without having to re-key it,&quot;said Bill Lukens, Cognos' district manager.andM;Users don't have to know a query language to operate the 20/20 DatabaseConnection, since English menus and prompts advise users and help them tobuild queries.andP;  The information is placed directly into the spreadsheet oncea query is finished, and access to the database is read-only, so that theinformation in the database cannot be compromised through use of the 20/20bridge, company officials said.andP;  Customized support features included in theDatabase Connection for PowerHouse include activity logging, support for thePowerHouse Quiz query language, support for PowerHouse and data formatting,the subfiles use of named queries to give users unfamiliar with PowerHousethe ability to use the spreadsheet as a database reporting medium, andsupport for databases and file types, including PowerHouse StarBasedatafiles.andM;&quot;The Cognos relationship is a real nice [one],&quot; said Russell Gee, vicepresident of sales at Access.andP;  &quot;It helps to round out our VAX databaseofferings, and we will continue to develop relationship with majorapplication vendors in this marketplace.&quot;andM;The Database connection is available now.andP;  Prices range from $800 for aMicroVAX 2000 to $17,000 for the VAX 8978.andM;Access Technology Inc. is located at 6 Pleasant St., South Natick, MA 01760,(508) 655-9191.andM;Cognos is located at 2 Corporate Place, I-95, Peabody, MA 01960, (508)535-7350.andO;</TEXT></DOC>